# Parent inheritance (writing-only)

This project uses **agent brain lite** with a **writing-only** slice of the parent `agent-rules` brain.

## What is inherited

| Asset | Path |
|-------|------|
| Writing + honesty Cursor rules | `.cursor/rules/` (allowlisted; see `harness/parent_rules_manifest.json`) |
| Skills (including nonacademic writer) | `agent-brain-lite/30_system/SKILLS/` |
| Ops / learning | `40_operations/`, `memory_engine/` |
| Cursor docs | `.cursor/docs/` |

**Not inherited:** parent MCP (`symlink_mcp_json: false`), scholarly/reporting/statistics rules, `skills-auto-detect` (would pull research workflows).

## Skills to use for prose

1. `SKILL_nonacademic-writer.md` — outline → draft → polish
2. `SKILL_avoid-ai-formulations.md` — anti-AI phrasing
3. Rules: `writing-avoid-ai.mdc`, `writing-avoid-ai-extended.mdc`, `writing-hrvatski-pravopis.mdc`

## Read-only on parent

Do not modify files under `PARENT_BRAIN_PATH`. Edit project docs (`docs/bonton/`), `01_work/`, and lite wiki under `agent-brain-lite/knowledge/`.

## Re-link

```powershell
cd agent-brain-lite
python scripts/link_parent.py --parent "C:\Users\Admin\Documents\agent rules"
```

After re-link, confirm research rules stay excluded via `parent_rules_manifest.json` version `1.2-writing-only`.
